{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f4909853-4321-4564-b599-a38628e22516","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### What to change in your GitHub Actions workflow:\n\n**1. Add `id-token: write` permission:**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**2. Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step:**\n```yaml\n# Before (API key):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n\n# After (trusted publishing):\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\nNo `-k` / `--api-key` flag needed — the OIDC token is used automatically.\n\n**3. On nuget.org**, configure your package's trusted publisher:\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher, specifying your **repo owner**, **repo name**, and optionally the **workflow filename** and **environment**.\n\n**4. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once everything works.\n\n### Key points\n- The `id-token: write` permission is the critical piece — it lets the runner request an OIDC JWT.\n- Modern `dotnet` CLI (≥ 8.0.4xx SDK) and `nuget.exe` (≥ 6.10) support trusted publishing natively.\n- If you use a GitHub Actions **environment**, you can scope the trusted publisher to that environment for extra security.\n\nWant me to make these changes if you share your workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"05edc9a8-54e0-4a12-81ad-7afc9ce4a5d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. I can provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":488},"id":"e8b275ed-caf1-476f-bf15-05b6f68506c1","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:38:34.647Z","parentId":"845fda73-2304-4537-b7bc-0fed4cd52810"}
